## Javascript today
Today, the browsers are mostly compatible in how they interpret Javascript
- Internet Explorer mostly supports standard Javascript, as do other main browsers
- There remain some differences in implementation, but frameworks like JQuery easily smooth them out.
- JQuery provides a single set of code commands that work the same across browsers by translating them automatically to match the browser being used.
