## Neverending war
The browser wars never quite ended...
- Google's Chrome, first released in 2011, [maintains the lead](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Usage_share_of_web_browsers#Summary_tables), with Safari in second place by market share
- Mozilla, a non-profit foundation entrusted by Netscape to maintain their source code, continues to maintain its successor, Firefox - the third most popular web browser
- Brendan Eich, inventor of Javascript, has recently created the [Brave browser](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brave_(web_browser)) which attempts to change the way the web is funded through ads and behavior profiling
- With many of the old-timers unhappy with the way The Web turned out, and with corporate and nation-state actors battling for control, the future direction of The Web and the browsers is still uncertain

